reviews.text: Not good.... we regretted going and even more for ordering the Chefs menu (plus local beer). $110 US dollars and We left most of it because food just did not taste good.  Also, service was great for the first two courses, then we were forgotten in the back room corner. It took easily over another half hour before next course came out and that was after giving some wait staff (who were busy setting empty tables for dinner service ) some confused looks. Imagine taking one bite of a dish and because of the taste, not being able to force another bite, even though it was expensive.

The food was good. Service was pretty top notch as well. Both met the expectations of a Michelin star. They is until near the end of our dinner where the manager in charge of our table was changed out to an older gentleman who assumed we didn't understand Cantonese, and complained to himself that we should just hurry up so he can go home already. We arrived at 9, and ordered everything well before their last call at 9:45pm, so it's not like we came in last minute. Our total bill was $3500 for 3 people. We should be able to savor and enjoy our food like every else without being complained about by staff. All other staff was great. It was really this one guy that threw me for a loop.
good setting overall, with great food and service.  reasonably priced compared to other high end Chinese restaurants in HK

Good food, good place and good service!  Even the desserts r great too.  Peter always provide excellent service to his customers.  You can have family gathering, friends gathering of even dating as they have some seats with privacy.
Fair taste with good service
